com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core
Class SymbologyFactory

java.lang.Object
  com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core.SymbologyFactory

public class SymbologyFactory
extends java.lang.Object

Factory for obtaining symbology of any kind from several sources like.

  1. XMLEntity's that, at least, contains a full class name string property that defines which class handles such symbol.

Author:
jaume dominguez faus - jaume.dominguez@iver.es

createSymbolFromXML

public static ISymbol createSymbolFromXML(XMLEntity xml,
                                          java.lang.String defaultDescription)
Factory that allows to create ISymbol's from an ISymbol xml descriptor. A barely specific XMLEntity object. The string passed in the second argument is the description text that will be used in case no description is supplied by the symbol's xml descriptor.

Parameters:
xml, - the symbol's xml descriptor
defaultDescription, - a human readable description string for the symbol.
Returns:
ISymbol

public static IStyle createStyleFromXML(XMLEntity xml,

Factory that allows to create IStyle's from an IStyle xml descriptor. A barely specific XMLEntity object. The string passed in the second argument is the description text that will be used in case no description is supplied by the style's xml descriptor.

Parameters:
